 :tx/rationale "Create task: SWS-1: Implement SessionWorkingSet struct — the hot-page resident set for session temporal locality (INV-GUIDANCE-010). BACKGROUND: The session working set is the missing layer between eternal store (all datoms) and ephemeral agent (single context window). It tracks what the agent is actively engaging RIGHT NOW. STRUCT: SessionWorkingSet { active_tasks: Vec<EntityId> (from :task/status = in-progress), session_entity: Option<EntityId> (from find_active_session), session_start_wall: u64 (from :session/started-at), session_created_tasks: BTreeSet<EntityId> (tasks with created_at > session_start_wall), epic_siblings: BTreeSet<EntityId> (tasks sharing parent EPIC with any active task) }. CONSTRUCTION: SessionWorkingSet::from_store(store) computes all fields from store state. Pure function, no IO. The active_tasks field uses TaskStatus::InProgress filter on all_tasks(). The session_created_tasks field compares task.created_at against session_start_wall. The epic_siblings field follows :dep/from edges from active tasks to find parent EPICs, then collects all children. FORMAL PROPERTY: The working set is a MONOTONICALLY GROWING set within a session (tasks are added via braid go, never removed until braid done). Size bounded by total open tasks. TRACES TO: INV-GUIDANCE-010, ADR-GUIDANCE-009. FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/guidance.rs. ACCEPTANCE: SessionWorkingSet::from_store on store with 3 in-progress tasks returns active_tasks.len() == 3."
